modelDescription: Candles are the historic rates for a product. Rates are returned in grouped buckets. Candle schema is of the form `[timestamp, price_low, price_high, price_open, price_close]`

endpoints.description: Candles will return historic rates for a product.

queryParams.description: Granularity is one of the following values: {60, 300, 900, 3600, 21600, 86400}. Otherwise, your request will be rejected. These values correspond to timeslices representing one minute, five minutes, fifteen minutes, one hour, six hours, and one day, respectively.
Start is a timestamp for starting range of aggregations.
End is a timestamp for ending range of aggregations.
